## Actions
- Built a py3.12 test venv (system python is 3.14, which breaks tiktoken):
  uv venv --python 3.12 --clear && uv sync --group test. Verified fake import.
- Monitors: CH obj_create calls validate_monitor_query_fields(base, leaf, val)
  (clickhouse_trace_server_batched.py:2002) right after validate_expected_digest.
  That helper (calls_query_builder/monitor_query_validation.py) is fully
  backend-agnostic — it compiles the query via process_query_to_conditions to
  surface bad fields (InvalidFieldError w/ allowed list) or structural errors
  (InvalidRequest), and early-returns for non-Monitor/opaque/absent queries. So
  the fake just had to call it identically; digest_result already carries
  base/leaf_object_class + processed_val. Drop-in.
- refs_read_batch: mirrored CH:5830 — collect ALL missing base-object digests
  and raise RefObjectsNotFoundError(msg, missing_object_digests) instead of the
  old per-ref NotFoundError. Added _obj_ref_target_exists() which checks
  existence INCLUDING soft-deleted (a deleted object is 'found' and reads back
  as None via _read_internal_obj_ref, NOT missing) — matches CH include_deleted.

