## Hints for Future Agents
- validate_monitor_query_fields runs on EVERY obj_create; it early-returns for
  non-Monitor objects, so the cost is one isinstance-ish check. Don't gate it.
- _obj_exists() excludes soft-deleted; do NOT use it for ref-missing detection
  (a deleted object would wrongly be 'missing'). Use _obj_ref_target_exists.
- RefObjectsNotFoundError(message, missing_object_digests: list[str]) — the test
  asserts on .missing_object_digests.

## Codebase Discoveries
- monitor_query_validation is deliberately backend-agnostic (no DB call; pure
  query compilation), so the fake reuses it verbatim.

